full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/28/2023 Report Date: 01/04/90 TO: HENRI HALL, MD Contract No. 21121 54 NE 54TH STREET Customer No. 1288576 MIAMI, FL 33137 **** USA FROM: SPECIALIZED TESTING SERVICES - a division of NABI 16500 N.W. 15th AVENUE MIAMI, FL 33169 A diagnosis of syphilis should not be made on the basis of a single reactive result without the support of patient history or positive clinical evidence. In those cases where clinical manifestation or history do not agree with laboratory results, treponemal tests should be performed to verify presence of syphilitic antibody.
